                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.711/89: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-22T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 22, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 22—6:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1376. Shanghai’s December 21, noon, regarding <hi rend="italic">Far Eastern
                        Review</hi>. I assume that action by Chinese Government was taken for the
                    purpose of punishing its owner and editor who has gone to Geneva as an adviser
                    to the government of Manchukuo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
